    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I've just updated the PR with last changes: \r\n\r\n* never unmount widgets but instead compute a boolean `canRefine` that is provided to widgets. Those widgets will display a new classname if no refinement present. Some, if a panel wrap them, will notify it. \r\n\r\nI removed the display:none from our default style, but still don't really know how to move forward. It still makes sense to hide panel for some widgets (ex: the RefinementList), and for others maybe not: (ex: RangeInput). Maybe we can do nothing about it in our default theme as for now, and discuss about the right implementation with the design team? End users will still be able to do what they want with our widgets in their side. What do you think?",
